Combine the mayonnaise, sour cream, sherry, and lemon juice in the slow cooker, whisking until smooth. Cover and cook on LOW until the dip is hot throughout, 1Â½ to 2 hours. Fold in the parsley and crabmeat and season with salt and white pepper. Cover and leave on LOW for another 20 minutes to heat the crab. Set the slow cooker in the entertaining area. Set on LOW, leave the cover off, and dip the bread cubes.